OL,3,CTravel disruption as Tube drivers
OL,4,Cstage second strike of the week
OL,6,FResearch by communications firm 02
OL,7,Fshowed that footfall in London was
OL,8,Fdown by up 12% compared with a normal
OL,9,FThursday morning.
OL,11,FFootfall in the City was down by 9%,
OL,12,FKing's Cross by 12%, the West End by
OL,13,F5% and Westminster by 11%.
OL,15,FA Virgin Media O2 spokesperson said:
OL,16,F"As Tube strikes continue across
OL,17,FLondon, our mobility data shows
OL,18,Ffootfall remains down across some of
OL,19,Fthe city's busiest areas.
OL,26,@xD@AOU
